`,n.jsxs(e.li,{children:[n.jsxs(e.strong,{children:["Schema tracking via ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"pglite_ddl"}),"."]})," A ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"cache-server init"})," installs an upstream event trigger that calls ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"pg_logical_emit_message(true, 'pglite_ddl', '')"})," on every DDL — a content-less signal riding the slot (pgoutput ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"messages 'true'"}),"). On receipt, the replica re-introspects the published schema and applies a structured delta. Additive changes (new column, new table) auto-apply; incompatible ones halt with a precise reason."]}),`
`,n.jsxs(e.li,{children:[n.jsx(e.strong,{children:"Security catalog mirrored by introspect-and-rebuild."})," Roles, role memberships, ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"SELECT"})," grants, RLS enable/force flags, and policies are NOT carried by any logical-replication stream. They are pulled in by a separate idempotent reconcile that fires on backfill, on the ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"pglite_ddl"})," signal, and on a periodic role poll. Roles are rebuilt as ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"NOLOGIN NOBYPASSRLS"})," shells; the application-side ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"query_as(role, claims, sql, params)"})," seam uses ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"SET LOCAL ROLE"})," inside a pinned transaction so the load-bearing RLS guarantee holds even if the pool's ",n.jsx(e.code,{children:"RESET ALL"})," is incomplete."]}),`
